# Architecture

## Stack

Artifact Guesser is a Next.js 13 application using the pages router.

- **Frontend**: React 18, Emotion CSS-in-JS, Tailwind CSS, styled-components
- **Backend**: Next.js API routes (pages/api/), Node.js runtime
- **Database**: MongoDB Atlas (single cluster, env-driven database name)
- **Auth**: iron-session (cookie-based, `monolith_auth` cookie)
- **Payments**: Stripe (subscriptions, webhooks)
- **Email**: Mailjet (transactional emails, BCC to admin)
- **Real-time**: Socket.IO (multiplayer games, global chat)
- **Analytics**: First-party event system (replaced GoatCounter)
- **OG Images**: @vercel/og (edge runtime, dynamic PNG generation)
- **3D**: Three.js + React Three Fiber (artifact visualization, experimental)

## Database

Single MongoDB Atlas cluster: `urcontext.rbv44f0.mongodb.net`

Database name is controlled by `MONGODB_DATABASE` environment variable:
- Production: `production` (default fallback)
- Staging/Dev: `staging`
- Tests: `ag_test` (MongoMemoryServer, ephemeral)

Connection is managed via `src/lib/apiUtils/mongoclient.js`:
- Development: global variable caching across HMR reloads
- Production: new connection per cold start, pooled (maxPoolSize: 10)

### Collections

| Collection | Purpose | Key Fields |
|---|---|---|
| accounts | User profiles | email, username, password (bcrypt), role, currentMode, currentTimer, subscription |
| games | Personal game records | userId, round, rounds, score, mode, roundData[], ongoing |
| artifacts | Museum artifacts (~135K) | name, location, time, images, isHighlight, problematic, source |
| dailyChallenges | One per day: 3 artifact IDs | dateKey (unique), artifactIds[], rounds |
| dailyGames | Per-user daily game state | userId + dateKey (unique), score, completed, roundData[] |
| challenges | Friend challenge definitions | dateKey, artifactIds[], challengerScore, challengerUsername |
| analyticsEvents | All tracked events | type, occurredAt, path, anonymousId, sessionId, userId, ip |
| favorites | User favorited artifacts | userId, artifactId |
| chat_messages | Global chat history | lobby, username, message, timestamp, id |
| platform | Platform-wide counters | noauthGames |

## API Routes

52 routes under `src/pages/api/`. All use `withSessionRoute()` wrapper for session access.

### Auth Pattern
```
const user = verifyAuth(req, res)        // Returns user or sends 401
const user = verifyAuth(req, res, ['Admin'])  // Role-based, sends 403
```

### Route Categories
- **Public (13)**: artifact browsing, daily challenge (anon), random artifact, OG images, Stripe webhooks
- **Auth-required (34)**: game CRUD, account management, favorites, daily game submission
- **Admin-only (2)**: mass email, daily reset
- **Edge runtime (1)**: `/api/og/daily` (OG image generation)

## Authentication

iron-session with cookie-based auth:
- Cookie: `monolith_auth`
- Encryption: `SESSION_PASSWORD` env var (32+ chars)
- JWT tokens signed with `SECRET` env var for internal use
- Passwords hashed with bcryptjs

### Known Issues
- `login.js`: admin bypass check has JS precedence bug (`!existingSession?.role === 'admin'`)
- `signup.js`: no duplicate username validation
- `games/current.js`: calls `verifyAuth(req)` without `res`, crashes with 500 instead of 401

## Frontend Architecture

### Game State
- `GameProvider` (`src/components/game/GameProvider.js`): manages personal game state via React context
- `DailyProvider` (`src/components/daily/DailyProvider.js`): manages daily challenge state
- `ChallengeProvider` (`src/components/daily/ChallengeProvider.js`): manages friend challenge state
- All three share the same context shape (round, score, artifact, guessed, timer state)

### Routing
- `/` — personal game (5-round, resumable)
- `/daily` — Today's Run (3-round daily challenge)
- `/challenge/[id]` — friend challenge with score comparison
- `/multiplayer/[lobbyid]` — real-time multiplayer
- `/dashboard` — admin dashboard (analytics, accounts, games, artifacts)
- `/support` — supporter page (Stripe plans)
- `/artifacts` — artifact database browser
- `/about` — about page

### Key Patterns
- `dynamic(() => ..., { ssr: false })` for game components (client-only rendering)
- SWR for data fetching with axios
- Emotion CSS prop + Tailwind classes (mixed, both in use)
- `useHotkeys` for keyboard shortcuts (Enter/Space to advance)
